# Cursor Rules for Personal Website

## Link Management
When adding external links to HTML files:
- Ensure they are properly formatted with `target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"` for external links
- After adding new external links, run `python3 tests/extract_links.py` to update the outbound links list
- The outbound links list is maintained in `tests/outbound_links.txt` for debugging and validation

## Testing
- Before committing, run `./tests/check_links.sh` to validate all external links
- The link validation tool uses lychee and can be integrated into CI/CD pipelines

## Code Style
- Use semantic HTML5
- Keep CSS and JavaScript minimal and vanilla
- Maintain the intentionally minimalistic design philosophy

## Investing page (portfolio + short options)
- Put **short calls** (and similar listed option overlays) on the **same `portfolio-card`** as the underlying security, not in a separate card.
- Use `<ul class="portfolio-overlays">` with a `<li>` per overlay; each line must include `<span class="portfolio-pct">…</span>` so `investing-sector-chart.js` aggregates the full weight for that sector.

## Library (`library.html`)
- When adding or editing a book entry, ask: **"When did you finish reading this book?"** If the user provides a month and year, append it to the `<li>` after the author(s), using ` – finished [Month] [Year]` (e.g. ` – finished Apr 2026`). If they skip it or the book is not yet finished, omit that suffix.
